- At most farmer's markets
- Online at Amazon and Walmart

.

The Los Nietos Board of Trustees and Superintendent have decided to follow the LA County Office of Education's recommendation to extend student dismissal through Monday, May 4th, to help stop the spread of COVID-19. At the moment, students are scheduled to return on Tuesday, May 5th.

Student meals will be served on Mondays and Wednesdays at all four school sites beginning the week of March 30th from 9:00 a.m. - 10:30 a.m.

We are working with our principals and teachers to provide students online instruction and will soon provide further information. We thank our staff and our families for your continued support throughout these uncertain times. We encourage you to continue following the stay at home order and practice social distancing at all times.

🔗For more information, please visit: https://www.losnietos.k12.ca.us/apps/news/article/1198461.

🔗Para leer en español visite: https://4.files.edl.io/53d0/03/27/20/145051-55690c4c-1086-4580-9208-1ac1d1a60d2a.pdf
.
.
#LosNietosSD #COVID19

#Highlight: We are thrilled to announce that 6 interns have joined Los Nietos School District to support our elementary teachers in implementing health and physical education curriculum.

Our first shout out goes to Nadia Guadagnini-Altamirano!

Nadia has worked with youth for the past 10 years teaching them gymnastics. She brings a great amount of energy and she is passionate about helping youth understand what health means to them. She aspires to become a Health Educator.

Thank you, Nadia for helping us create a healthy Los Nietos!
.
.
#LosNietosSD #HealthEducation #PhysicalEducation #CalPolyPomona #Kinesiology #CalPolyPomonaKinesiology

post_text:
Help us congratulate the 2019 Community Service Award Recipient, Mrs. Rita Cerna!

Mrs. Cerna has been a member of the Los Nietos School District community for the past 28 years. She began as a volunteer at our district office, has served on the School Site Council at Aeolian Elementary School and has been a long-standing member of our Parent Teacher Club.

After thirteen years of being involved as a parent, Mrs. Cerna started to work for our district as a Noon Duty Supervisor and has served in this position ever since while still being a Superstar Volunteer. To this day, we don't think she has ever said, "No."

Thank you Mrs. Cerna for all of your hard work and commitment these past 28 years!
.
.
#LosNietosSD #CommunityInvolvement #Volunteers #Award #Education #K12Schools #Aeolian_ES #ElemSchools
